description:
PostProcessing.js currently detects WebGPU and falls back to direct render (no EffectComposer), bypassing bloom entirely. When WebGPU is active the Sun has no glow/bloom effect.

Fix: Use Three.js WebGPU-native post-processing pipeline.

  import { bloom } from 'three/tsl'
  import { PostProcessing } from 'three/webgpu'

  const postProcessing = new PostProcessing(renderer)
  const scenePass = pass(scene, camera)
  const bloomPass = bloom(scenePass, 1.8, 0.5, 0.8)
  postProcessing.outputNode = bloomPass

Three.js >= 0.170 already installed. The bloom TSL node works natively with WebGPURenderer without falling back to WebGL EffectComposer.

Current code: src/renderer/PostProcessing.js — isWebGPU branch sets this.enabled=false and calls renderer.render(scene, camera) directly.
